1 percent (3%) of the allowance payable on June 1, 2025, in accordance with subsection (k) of this
2 section. Effective July 1, 2025, the retirement allowance payable to, or on account of,
3 beneficiaries whose retirement commenced after July 1, 2024, but before June 30, 2025, is
4 increased by a prorated amount of three percent (3%), as determined by the Board of Trustees
5 based upon the number of months that a retirement allowance was paid between July 1, 2024,
6 and June 30, 2025."
7 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Reserve for Retiree
8 Cost-of-Living Adjustments the sum of two hundred fifty million dollars ($250,000,000) in
9 recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to implement Section 1 of this act.
10 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
